<br>
No, I will accept many reasons for going to war.  However, going in to force a revolution on a culture is the wrong reason.  But, right now that's the best reason we've been given, the other being &quot;Fear&quot; (ie, fear of future terrorist attacks) which is even a worse reason in my mind for killing so many people.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I know it's hard to imagine that anyone might be happy in a culture or government such as the one in Iraq; however, take it from someone who grew up in abject poverty here in the rural south of the U.S:   you can be perfectly happy and content in any situation given that you believe that God intended it to be that way.   These folks we're fighting have a STRONG belief in their religion and no matter how good we think we are, they tend to believe that we're after them and their government because of their faith.   I know that's not true, you know it's not true....but it really doesn't matter....<br>
<br>
I know that if an army of predominantly Muslims suddenly attacked southern Georgia in the U.S, the men and women and children there would probably fight to the death before giving up....    NEVER underestimate religion....<br>
<br>
We may have forgotten the Crusades, but I can assure you that many in this part of the world have not.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aelorean>Aelorean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/03 1:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.simpson.edu/~mcmahan/temp/ael4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I just don't fucking get it.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
